annotation_report.Description: yeast selectable marker conferring kanamycin resistance (Wach et al., 1994)
aminoglycoside phosphotransferase; aph(3')-Ia; confers resistance to kanamycin
β-lactamase; bla; confers resistance to ampicillin, carbenicillin, and related antibiotics
promoter for bacteriophage SP6 RNA polymerase
promoter for bacteriophage T7 RNA polymerase
basis of mobility region from pBR322
Rop protein, which maintains plasmids at low copy number; rop
modified intron A from human cytomegalovirus (CMV)
lac repressor; lacI; The lac repressor binds to the lac operator to inhibit transcription in E. coli. This inhibition can be relieved by adding lactose or isopropyl-β-D-thiogalactopyranoside (IPTG).

MRL1_ASHGO - Protein inferred from homology: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 3. Sorting receptor involved in the transport of vacuolar enzymes from the Golgi complex to the vacuole. From Ashbya gossypii (strain ATCC 10895 / CBS 109.51 / FGSC 9923 / NRRL Y-1056) (Yeast) (Eremothecium gossypii).
